This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase

Created attachment 1171954 patch to fix some compilation issues
For the record, here's a patch to fix some of the compilation issues with gcc-6: https://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/beignet/2016-May/007498.html
Latest version of Beignet seems to build for x86_64: http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=15248778
